WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.700
and preached and had meetings

00:00:02.700 --> 00:00:04.880
and then got back, I think Monday night,

00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:06.079
and then you leave again on Saturday,

00:00:06.079 --> 00:00:08.079
if I understand, remember correctly.

00:00:08.079 --> 00:00:11.039
And so you pray for them as they're out ministering.

00:00:11.039 --> 00:00:13.680
And someone asked me the other day,

00:00:13.680 --> 00:00:15.039
they said, oh, the Sommerdorfs are here.

00:00:15.039 --> 00:00:15.880
I said, well,

00:00:17.479 --> 00:00:20.620
their RV is here, but they're not here.

00:00:20.620 --> 00:00:23.799
And they're having meetings and what have you,

00:00:23.799 --> 00:00:25.719
but it's good that we can see you this evening.

00:00:25.719 --> 00:00:27.860
So thank you for being here.

00:00:27.860 --> 00:00:29.059
Amen, amen.

00:00:29.059 --> 00:00:30.360
Romans chapter number 10

00:00:30.360 --> 00:00:32.500
is where we're gonna kick it off this evening.

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:33.659
Romans chapter 10,

00:00:33.659 --> 00:00:35.299
it's a familiar passage of scripture.

00:00:35.299 --> 00:00:37.840
On Sunday, I preached a couple of messages

00:00:37.840 --> 00:00:39.340
about missions conference

00:00:39.340 --> 00:00:41.740
and really kind of a missions emphasis.

00:00:41.740 --> 00:00:43.680
And in fact, on Sunday evening,

00:00:43.680 --> 00:00:47.520
we examined the last part of Acts 14.

00:00:47.520 --> 00:00:50.779
I've often referred to that portion of scripture

00:00:50.779 --> 00:00:53.319
as the first missions conference.

00:00:53.319 --> 00:00:57.020
And those that were sent out from the church at Antioch,

00:00:57.020 --> 00:00:59.880
they completed, they fulfilled their ministry

00:00:59.880 --> 00:01:01.880
that God had called them to,

00:01:01.880 --> 00:01:04.220
and they returned back to Antioch

00:01:04.220 --> 00:01:06.199
and the church was gathered together.

00:01:06.199 --> 00:01:10.000
They rehearsed all that God did with them and through them

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:13.559
and how God had opened the door to the Gentiles

00:01:13.559 --> 00:01:15.959
and just amazing things were taking place

00:01:15.959 --> 00:01:17.480
and we're rejoicing.

00:01:17.480 --> 00:01:21.040
And this evening, just wanna answer this question.

00:01:21.040 --> 00:01:23.279
I've really just titled the message tonight

00:01:23.279 --> 00:01:26.379
with a question, why have a missions conference?

00:01:26.540 --> 00:01:27.940
Why do we do this?

00:01:27.940 --> 00:01:31.339
Why do we go through all of the expense

00:01:31.339 --> 00:01:33.339
and all of the planning

00:01:33.339 --> 00:01:36.019
to be able to have a missions conference?

00:01:36.019 --> 00:01:38.319
Oftentimes, I've scheduled,

00:01:38.319 --> 00:01:40.419
in fact, our missions conference for next year,

00:01:40.419 --> 00:01:42.559
the keynote speaker's already scheduled.

00:01:42.559 --> 00:01:44.760
And we have our keynote speaker

00:01:44.760 --> 00:01:47.459
scheduled a year or two in advance

00:01:47.459 --> 00:01:49.860
and we go through the planning and all of that.

00:01:49.860 --> 00:01:52.739
And why is it, why do we have booklets that we provide?

00:01:52.739 --> 00:01:54.400
Why do we do all of these things,

00:01:54.400 --> 00:01:57.400
come up with a theme and artwork and so on and so forth?

00:01:57.400 --> 00:01:59.019
And so this evening for a few minutes,

00:01:59.019 --> 00:02:01.639
I wanna try to answer that question for you

00:02:01.639 --> 00:02:04.739
and then we'll have some concentrated prayer time

00:02:04.739 --> 00:02:07.319
specifically with regard to our missions conference.

00:02:07.319 --> 00:02:09.479
But I wanna look here at Romans chapter 10

00:02:09.479 --> 00:02:12.839
for just a few moments before I answer that question.

00:02:12.839 --> 00:02:14.639
Notice this truth in verse 13.

00:02:14.639 --> 00:02:17.160
I believe tonight that most of us

00:02:17.160 --> 00:02:20.039
could probably quote Romans 10, 13.

00:02:20.039 --> 00:02:23.720
For whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord

00:02:23.720 --> 00:02:25.759
shall be saved.

00:02:25.759 --> 00:02:27.759
Isn't that a wonderful verse?

00:02:27.759 --> 00:02:29.679
I mean, it's precious, is it not?

00:02:29.679 --> 00:02:31.440
Every time, I believe every time

00:02:31.440 --> 00:02:33.259
I've ever shared the gospel with someone

00:02:33.259 --> 00:02:36.199
and was able to get through the entirety of the gospel,

00:02:36.199 --> 00:02:39.320
I end in Romans 10, 13 and say,

00:02:39.320 --> 00:02:41.919
for whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord

00:02:41.919 --> 00:02:42.759
shall be saved.

00:02:42.759 --> 00:02:45.559
That means you, that means anyone.

00:02:45.559 --> 00:02:48.240
And God said that if you would call on him,

00:02:48.240 --> 00:02:49.639
he will save you.

00:02:49.639 --> 00:02:53.000
And what a blessing this verse of scripture is.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:54.960
But we find that the text continues

00:02:54.960 --> 00:02:57.279
and notice in verse 14,

00:02:57.279 --> 00:03:01.279
how then shall they call on him

00:03:01.279 --> 00:03:04.139
in whom they have not believed?

00:03:04.139 --> 00:03:07.479
And how shall they believe in him

00:03:07.479 --> 00:03:11.199
of whom they have not heard?

00:03:11.199 --> 00:03:14.919
And how shall they hear without a preacher?

00:03:14.919 --> 00:03:19.919
Aren't those some soul piercing questions?

00:03:20.240 --> 00:03:24.440
I mean, for us as believers to read the questions

00:03:24.440 --> 00:03:27.479
in verse number 14 and thought provoking,

00:03:27.479 --> 00:03:29.000
it ends in verse 14,

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:33.080
how shall they hear without a preacher?

00:03:33.080 --> 00:03:34.520
Obviously this evening,

00:03:34.520 --> 00:03:38.360
we know that someone had to share the gospel with us.

00:03:38.360 --> 00:03:40.720
Someone told you about Jesus.

00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:42.639
It may have been your mom, it may have been your dad,

00:03:42.639 --> 00:03:43.899
it may have been a grandparent,

00:03:43.899 --> 00:03:46.440
it may have been a pastor, it may have been a coworker,

00:03:46.440 --> 00:03:48.199
it may have been a missionary,

00:03:48.240 --> 00:03:50.360
it may have been a stranger that just knocked on your door,

00:03:50.360 --> 00:03:53.800
but the reality is that somebody told you

00:03:53.800 --> 00:03:57.520
and somebody told me about Jesus.

00:03:57.520 --> 00:04:00.119
And we find this evening that that question,

00:04:00.119 --> 00:04:03.639
how shall they hear without a preacher?

00:04:03.639 --> 00:04:07.339
We understand that government is established by God,

00:04:07.339 --> 00:04:11.119
but government has not been given the responsibility

00:04:11.119 --> 00:04:12.759
of preaching the gospel.

00:04:12.759 --> 00:04:14.039
Now it's okay if they decide

00:04:14.039 --> 00:04:15.119
they're gonna preach the gospel,

00:04:15.119 --> 00:04:18.000
but that's not what God instituted.

00:04:18.760 --> 00:04:21.760
God designed the church, those that are born again,

00:04:21.760 --> 00:04:23.480
saved by the grace of God,

00:04:23.480 --> 00:04:25.700
that we would be the ones that would proclaim

00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:27.720
the gospel of Jesus Christ.

00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:30.679
The Bible says in verse 15, continuing with a question,

00:04:30.679 --> 00:04:35.679
how and how shall they preach except they be sent?

00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:38.839
As it is written, how beautiful are the feet of them

00:04:38.839 --> 00:04:40.559
that preach the gospel of peace

00:04:40.559 --> 00:04:43.480
and bring glad tidings of good things.

00:04:43.480 --> 00:04:46.279
You know, the gospel that we preach is a gospel of peace.

00:04:46.279 --> 00:04:48.839
It's a gospel of glad tidings.

00:04:48.839 --> 00:04:50.279
The word means good news.

00:04:50.279 --> 00:04:53.399
I understand that not everyone receives it as such.

00:04:53.399 --> 00:04:56.079
I understand that not everyone is excited

00:04:56.079 --> 00:04:58.339
to receive the gospel,

00:04:58.339 --> 00:05:01.480
but how can a man have peace with God?

00:05:02.359 --> 00:05:04.040
Only through Jesus Christ.

00:05:04.040 --> 00:05:06.200
In fact, earlier in the book of Romans,

00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:09.640
we read that very thing in verse number one of chapter five,

00:05:09.640 --> 00:05:12.519
therefore being justified by faith,

00:05:12.519 --> 00:05:17.519
we have peace with God through our Lord Jesus Christ.

00:05:17.959 --> 00:05:19.760
And so we find that the message

00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:23.760
that the preacher is delivering is a message of peace.

00:05:23.760 --> 00:05:27.519
It's a message of glad tidings of good things.

00:05:27.519 --> 00:05:28.760
And it says in verse 16,

00:05:28.760 --> 00:05:30.619
but they have not all obeyed the gospel,

00:05:30.619 --> 00:05:33.640
for Isaiah saith, Lord, who hath believed our report?

00:05:33.640 --> 00:05:35.000
So then faith cometh by hearing

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:38.119
and hearing by the word of God.

00:05:38.119 --> 00:05:39.920
As we look at this passage of scripture,

00:05:39.920 --> 00:05:43.040
we're reminded this evening of a wonderful promise,

00:05:43.040 --> 00:05:45.359
one that we hold dear to our hearts,

00:05:45.359 --> 00:05:47.440
for whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord

00:05:47.440 --> 00:05:49.000
shall be saved.

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:50.859
But after that wonderful promise,

00:05:50.859 --> 00:05:55.640
we're confronted with some convicting questions,

00:05:55.640 --> 00:05:57.679
some thought provoking questions.

00:05:57.679 --> 00:06:01.200
And one of those, as we've mentioned already,

00:06:01.200 --> 00:06:02.720
how shall they hear without a preacher?

00:06:02.720 --> 00:06:05.320
How shall they preach except they be sent?

00:06:05.320 --> 00:06:06.760
As you see the end of verse 14

00:06:06.760 --> 00:06:08.559
and the beginning of verse 15.

00:06:08.559 --> 00:06:10.320
And so as we enter into Missions Conference

00:06:10.320 --> 00:06:11.739
and seek to answer this question,

00:06:11.739 --> 00:06:12.899
why a Missions Conference?

00:06:12.899 --> 00:06:14.959
Why do we put it on the schedule?

00:06:14.959 --> 00:06:18.399
Why do these families travel thousands and thousands

00:06:18.399 --> 00:06:21.299
of miles throughout their time of deputation

00:06:21.299 --> 00:06:24.220
to visit from church to church, to church to church,

00:06:24.220 --> 00:06:27.019
to stand up and present and to have their children,

00:06:27.019 --> 00:06:29.079
all those things, why do we do it?

00:06:29.079 --> 00:06:31.640
And let me just give you a few thoughts this evening.

00:06:31.640 --> 00:06:35.579
Number one, it is an opportunity to be reminded.

00:06:35.579 --> 00:06:37.559
A Missions Conference is an opportunity

00:06:37.559 --> 00:06:39.200
for us to be reminded.

00:06:39.200 --> 00:06:40.179
Reminded of what?

00:06:40.179 --> 00:06:44.519
Well, reminded that Jesus is the only hope for the world.

00:06:44.519 --> 00:06:47.420
To be reminded that the world is big.

00:06:47.420 --> 00:06:49.959
I know sometimes we say it's so small.

00:06:49.959 --> 00:06:51.739
Well, it's also so large.

00:06:51.739 --> 00:06:55.920
There's 8.2 billion people in the world today.

00:06:55.920 --> 00:06:58.239
There are places all around the globe.

00:06:58.239 --> 00:07:00.239
We look at a map, we look at a globe,

00:07:00.239 --> 00:07:03.820
and we are reminded that we live in a world

00:07:03.820 --> 00:07:05.480
that is full of people.

00:07:05.480 --> 00:07:08.640
And there's a great need.

00:07:08.640 --> 00:07:12.959
We're reminded that everywhere, all people everywhere

00:07:12.959 --> 00:07:14.640
need to hear the gospel.

00:07:14.640 --> 00:07:17.440
There have been times in which we've had Missions Conference

00:07:17.440 --> 00:07:21.299
and we've had folks come from various places

00:07:21.299 --> 00:07:23.239
and they're coming and maybe we're familiar

00:07:23.239 --> 00:07:26.799
with the particular country in which they're going to.

00:07:26.799 --> 00:07:29.279
Guyana, I don't know how many of you knew

00:07:29.279 --> 00:07:32.160
or know where Guyana is.

00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:34.679
That's one of the missionary families.

00:07:34.679 --> 00:07:35.920
Now, Switzerland, you say, okay,

00:07:35.920 --> 00:07:37.720
I'm familiar with Switzerland.

00:07:37.720 --> 00:07:40.079
Guyana, we had a missionary a number of years ago

00:07:40.079 --> 00:07:41.440
that was coming to be with us

00:07:41.440 --> 00:07:43.839
and they were going to the Gambia.

00:07:43.839 --> 00:07:45.679
I'd never heard of the Gambia.

00:07:45.679 --> 00:07:48.079
And what did I do?

00:07:48.079 --> 00:07:50.519
Well, I went to Google because Google knows everything.

00:07:50.519 --> 00:07:53.279
And that's, I'm kidding, Google doesn't know everything.

00:07:53.279 --> 00:07:54.880
And it thinks it does.

00:07:54.880 --> 00:07:57.239
But I went to Google and I looked up the Gambia

00:07:57.239 --> 00:07:58.839
and called the missionary back

00:07:58.839 --> 00:08:00.079
because they left me a voicemail

00:08:00.079 --> 00:08:01.559
and began to talk to him about the Gambia.

00:08:01.559 --> 00:08:03.200
And he said, you're like the first preacher

00:08:03.200 --> 00:08:06.480
that I've talked to that knew where the Gambia is

00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:07.440
and all of this sort of thing.

00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:08.799
And I said, well, I cheated.

00:08:08.799 --> 00:08:10.320
And I looked it up.

00:08:10.320 --> 00:08:12.679
But the reality is that there are places

00:08:12.679 --> 00:08:15.040
that we're not familiar with.

00:08:15.040 --> 00:08:18.079
And we're reminded that there's a need there.

00:08:18.079 --> 00:08:20.480
There are people there.

00:08:20.480 --> 00:08:25.160
And we're reminded that not only are there people

00:08:25.160 --> 00:08:28.119
in these places, we'll be reminded about Guyana,

00:08:28.119 --> 00:08:30.200
we'll be reminded about Switzerland.

00:08:30.200 --> 00:08:32.960
We don't have missionaries in either one of those countries

00:08:33.719 --> 00:08:34.559
that we currently support.

00:08:34.559 --> 00:08:36.400
And we'll be reminded about the need there,

00:08:36.400 --> 00:08:39.840
but we'll also be reminded through every missions conference

00:08:39.840 --> 00:08:42.440
that we've ever had, through every directory

00:08:42.440 --> 00:08:44.479
that you ever look at, through every button

00:08:44.479 --> 00:08:46.200
you ever push on that map,

00:08:46.200 --> 00:08:50.039
you will not find a missionary to Northern Virginia.

00:08:51.320 --> 00:08:53.599
Because we're reminded that we are the missionaries

00:08:53.599 --> 00:08:55.280
to Northern Virginia.

00:08:55.280 --> 00:08:56.840
This is our Jerusalem.

00:08:56.840 --> 00:08:59.000
This is our responsibility.

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:02.440
This is our place of ministry.

00:09:02.440 --> 00:09:06.599
And we're reminded, as we have a missions conference,

00:09:06.599 --> 00:09:09.840
we're reminded that we have a responsibility.

00:09:09.840 --> 00:09:12.520
And I often say to you that I like to look at it

00:09:12.520 --> 00:09:15.799
more as being a privilege than a responsibility.

00:09:15.799 --> 00:09:18.239
Because when we focus too much on the responsibility,

00:09:18.239 --> 00:09:22.039
we almost can get into that duty mindset, I have to.

00:09:22.039 --> 00:09:24.359
But the reality is that sharing the gospel

00:09:24.359 --> 00:09:29.359
is a get to situation, not necessarily a have to situation.

00:09:29.440 --> 00:09:31.119
Now, I believe you have to.

00:09:31.119 --> 00:09:32.719
We're commanded to.

00:09:32.719 --> 00:09:36.320
But I get to tell people about my Jesus

00:09:36.320 --> 00:09:39.080
and about how wonderful he is and what he's done for me

00:09:39.080 --> 00:09:40.760
and how he's changed my life.

00:09:40.760 --> 00:09:42.719
And so when we have a missions conference,

00:09:42.719 --> 00:09:47.039
it's an opportunity for us to be reminded of some things.

00:09:47.039 --> 00:09:48.760
There will be some that will be present

00:09:48.760 --> 00:09:51.359
for a missions conference, even as I mentioned on Sunday,

00:09:51.359 --> 00:09:53.400
that this will be their very first missions conference

00:09:53.400 --> 00:09:56.039
they've ever participated in in any church anywhere.

00:09:57.159 --> 00:09:59.679
And they will be new to the whole thing

00:09:59.679 --> 00:10:03.259
will be reminded of some things that maybe for them

00:10:03.259 --> 00:10:06.419
will be new to them or it's just a reminder to you,

00:10:06.419 --> 00:10:07.939
you've already known it,

00:10:07.939 --> 00:10:10.379
but the reality is that we're prone to forget.

00:10:11.779 --> 00:10:13.959
You know, God says to the children of Israel,

00:10:13.959 --> 00:10:16.659
beware lest thou forget.

00:10:16.659 --> 00:10:19.339
In the context in Deuteronomy chapter six,

00:10:19.339 --> 00:10:21.459
he gives them that warning

00:10:21.459 --> 00:10:23.499
of when they are increased with goods,

00:10:23.499 --> 00:10:25.059
they have homes that they didn't build,

00:10:25.059 --> 00:10:26.579
they have vineyards that they didn't plant,

00:10:26.579 --> 00:10:30.019
all of these things, beware lest thou forget the Lord.

00:10:30.019 --> 00:10:31.299
You know what happened with the church

00:10:31.299 --> 00:10:34.339
and as we look in Revelation chapter number three,

00:10:34.339 --> 00:10:36.319
the church of the Laodiceans,

00:10:36.319 --> 00:10:38.599
they were increased with goods, they had need of nothing,

00:10:38.599 --> 00:10:41.259
they needed to be reminded of some things

00:10:41.259 --> 00:10:43.579
and there's some times when we have a missions conference

00:10:43.579 --> 00:10:46.639
where it's a time, it's an opportunity to be reminded.

00:10:46.639 --> 00:10:51.539
Number two, it is an opportunity to refocus, to refocus.

00:10:51.539 --> 00:10:53.179
You ever hear somebody say something like this,

00:10:53.179 --> 00:10:55.099
you need to hit the reset button

00:10:55.099 --> 00:10:57.739
and sometimes we just need to hit the reset button,

00:10:57.739 --> 00:10:59.259
we need to refocus.

00:10:59.259 --> 00:11:03.459
I believe this evening that we live in a fast-paced society.

00:11:03.459 --> 00:11:04.819
Do you agree with that?

00:11:04.819 --> 00:11:07.059
I mean, we live in a fast-paced society.

00:11:07.059 --> 00:11:09.339
Eric and Christine and Levi have been visiting our church

00:11:09.339 --> 00:11:11.939
for a few weeks and they were over to our home

00:11:11.939 --> 00:11:14.859
on Monday evening for dinner and fellowship

00:11:14.859 --> 00:11:17.859
as we would try to get to know them and minister to them

00:11:17.859 --> 00:11:19.979
and one of the things that Christine said was,

00:11:19.979 --> 00:11:24.819
it's just so fast here, the pace of life is so fast.

00:11:25.539 --> 00:11:27.579
It is, it is.

00:11:27.579 --> 00:11:31.499
We live in a fast-paced society, we have many things,

00:11:31.499 --> 00:11:35.819
many things that are competing for our attention.

00:11:35.819 --> 00:11:40.539
They're competing for our focus and we're human beings,

00:11:40.539 --> 00:11:42.899
some of us have the ability to multitask

00:11:42.899 --> 00:11:45.739
and some of us don't but those of us

00:11:45.739 --> 00:11:47.659
that have the ability to multitask,

00:11:47.659 --> 00:11:49.739
you know what I find sometimes?

00:11:49.739 --> 00:11:54.339
The ability to multitask is almost a deficiency at times

00:11:54.339 --> 00:11:57.779
because you never can actually be fully focused

00:11:57.779 --> 00:11:58.739
on one thing, why?

00:11:58.739 --> 00:12:01.019
Because you're too busy multitasking

00:12:01.019 --> 00:12:05.059
and it's a help but it also can be a hindrance

00:12:05.059 --> 00:12:06.539
and I've learned that in my own life

00:12:06.539 --> 00:12:08.259
and so when we think about a missions conference,

00:12:08.259 --> 00:12:13.179
not only to be reminded but an opportunity to refocus

00:12:13.179 --> 00:12:15.259
and I think about the world that we live in

00:12:15.259 --> 00:12:16.819
and all the things that are going on

00:12:16.819 --> 00:12:19.539
and that are competing for your attention and my attention

00:12:19.539 --> 00:12:21.939
and sometimes we just need to have that reset,

00:12:21.939 --> 00:12:25.459
that refocus on what am I really here for?

00:12:25.459 --> 00:12:29.859
What is the purpose that God has for me?

00:12:29.859 --> 00:12:34.139
And when we have a few days with a purposed emphasis

00:12:34.139 --> 00:12:37.779
on missions, it helps us to refocus.

00:12:37.779 --> 00:12:40.659
It helps us to unplug a little bit and say,

00:12:40.659 --> 00:12:43.500
okay, here's where we need to be focused,

00:12:43.500 --> 00:12:45.699
this is where we gotta get our attention on.

00:12:45.699 --> 00:12:47.619
You know, the reality is it's so easy

00:12:47.619 --> 00:12:49.659
for us to be distracted.

00:12:49.659 --> 00:12:53.939
The enemy is good at keeping us distracted

00:12:53.939 --> 00:12:57.379
and we can be distracted with good things

00:12:57.379 --> 00:12:58.779
that aren't the best things.

00:12:59.979 --> 00:13:01.739
They don't have to be evil things

00:13:01.739 --> 00:13:03.539
or wicked things that distract us,

00:13:03.539 --> 00:13:07.259
they could be good things but they're not the best things

00:13:07.259 --> 00:13:08.819
and all of a sudden they get in the way

00:13:08.819 --> 00:13:11.500
and they cause us to lose our focus

00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:12.979
and we start going through life

00:13:12.979 --> 00:13:15.339
and we can almost begin to have the questions

00:13:15.339 --> 00:13:18.019
that lost people have of what am I here for?

00:13:18.019 --> 00:13:20.459
What's the purpose of this?

00:13:20.459 --> 00:13:23.059
The reality is that as God's people,

00:13:23.059 --> 00:13:26.779
we know that God has a specific purpose for us

00:13:26.779 --> 00:13:30.419
and there are times in which we just need to refocus.

00:13:30.419 --> 00:13:32.459
What is it that God has for me?

00:13:32.459 --> 00:13:33.459
What is the purpose?

00:13:33.459 --> 00:13:36.099
And so we take these days and we're not trying

00:13:36.099 --> 00:13:39.259
to wear you out but we take these days

00:13:39.259 --> 00:13:42.419
and place this emphasis and have this purpose,

00:13:42.419 --> 00:13:44.419
why, to be reminded of some things

00:13:44.419 --> 00:13:46.519
but also so that we can refocus.

00:13:46.519 --> 00:13:49.599
Can I tell you that as individuals we can get distracted

00:13:49.599 --> 00:13:50.759
but can I tell you this evening

00:13:50.759 --> 00:13:55.319
that as churches corporately we can get distracted?

00:13:55.319 --> 00:13:57.559
You know, there are churches that lose focus

00:13:57.559 --> 00:13:58.899
of what the mission is.

00:14:00.219 --> 00:14:03.959
There is a truth of outreach and ministry

00:14:03.959 --> 00:14:06.199
and outreach is to reach those that are without

00:14:06.199 --> 00:14:08.839
and ministry is to minister to those that are within

00:14:08.839 --> 00:14:11.079
and there's gotta be balance

00:14:11.079 --> 00:14:15.079
and the reality is that we can get so good

00:14:15.079 --> 00:14:18.079
at edifying the believers

00:14:18.079 --> 00:14:21.279
and so bad at evangelizing the lost

00:14:22.160 --> 00:14:25.399
and we have to recognize there's an ability,

00:14:25.399 --> 00:14:30.299
there's a possibility that churches,

00:14:31.160 --> 00:14:33.000
we can lose our focus

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:35.519
and not only as individuals or as families

00:14:35.519 --> 00:14:37.919
can we lose our focus but corporately

00:14:37.919 --> 00:14:39.679
we could lose our focus

00:14:39.679 --> 00:14:42.399
and so a missions conference gives us the opportunity

00:14:42.839 --> 00:14:44.539
to be reminded, to refocus.

00:14:44.539 --> 00:14:48.880
Number three, it gives us an opportunity to respond.

00:14:48.880 --> 00:14:52.199
James 1.22, turn over there, I know that you know it.

00:14:52.199 --> 00:14:55.639
It's a favorite verse of mine, I pray it so often.

00:14:55.639 --> 00:14:59.479
I pray it each day when I go to open God's word personally,

00:14:59.479 --> 00:15:01.119
when I have my devotions.

00:15:01.119 --> 00:15:02.959
I pray it almost every service

00:15:02.959 --> 00:15:05.679
that I open up a service in prayer.

00:15:05.679 --> 00:15:08.880
Why, because God gave us his word

00:15:08.880 --> 00:15:11.359
so that we would apply it, so that we would do it.

00:15:11.440 --> 00:15:13.239
He did not give us his word

00:15:13.239 --> 00:15:15.399
so that we could just answer questions

00:15:15.399 --> 00:15:19.039
and have some level of knowledge about what the Bible says.

00:15:19.039 --> 00:15:21.519
No, we are to be doers of the word

00:15:21.519 --> 00:15:24.160
and he says in James, notice in verse 22,

00:15:24.160 --> 00:15:28.519
but be doers of the word and not hearers only.

00:15:28.519 --> 00:15:32.660
Then notice this, deceiving your own selves.

00:15:32.660 --> 00:15:34.940
For if any man be a hearer of the word and not a doer,

00:15:34.940 --> 00:15:38.339
he is like unto a man beholding his natural face in a glass.

00:15:38.339 --> 00:15:40.500
For he beholdeth himself and goeth his way

00:15:40.500 --> 00:15:44.820
and straightway forgetteth what manner of man he was.

00:15:46.380 --> 00:15:49.220
Verse 25, but whoso looketh

00:15:49.220 --> 00:15:51.699
into the perfect law of liberty.

00:15:51.699 --> 00:15:53.940
Aren't you thankful that we have a Bible?

00:15:53.940 --> 00:15:56.059
It's the perfect law of liberty.

00:15:56.059 --> 00:15:58.859
The Bible says this and continueth therein.

00:15:58.859 --> 00:15:59.779
You know what the idea is?

00:15:59.779 --> 00:16:01.419
That we're applying it, we're doing it,

00:16:01.419 --> 00:16:05.940
we're continuing, we're applying the truth in our lives.

00:16:05.940 --> 00:16:09.139
He being not a forgetful hearer,

00:16:09.139 --> 00:16:11.859
but a doer of the work, this man,

00:16:11.859 --> 00:16:15.459
notice what it says, shall be blessed in his deed.

00:16:15.459 --> 00:16:17.100
Do you wanna be blessed?

00:16:17.100 --> 00:16:19.579
The blessing doesn't come just by hearing,

00:16:19.579 --> 00:16:22.419
the blessing comes by hearing and doing.

00:16:22.419 --> 00:16:26.299
Remember what God says to Joshua in Joshua chapter one.

00:16:26.299 --> 00:16:28.220
I know again, a verse of scripture

00:16:28.220 --> 00:16:30.979
that many of you have committed to memory,

00:16:30.979 --> 00:16:34.500
but the Bible says this, as God is preparing Joshua

00:16:34.500 --> 00:16:38.739
for entering into and leading the children of Israel,

00:16:39.179 --> 00:16:41.380
the book that he's being referred to

00:16:41.380 --> 00:16:43.500
is really the Pentateuch as we'd refer to it,

00:16:43.500 --> 00:16:45.419
the books of Moses.

00:16:46.419 --> 00:16:48.619
And in Joshua one and verse number eight,

00:16:48.619 --> 00:16:50.739
the Bible says this book of the law

00:16:50.739 --> 00:16:54.019
shall not depart out of thy mouth.

00:16:54.019 --> 00:16:54.940
But notice what he says,

00:16:54.940 --> 00:16:57.699
but thou shalt meditate therein day and night,

00:16:57.699 --> 00:17:00.739
that thou mayest observe, what does it say?

00:17:00.739 --> 00:17:05.459
To do according to all.

00:17:05.459 --> 00:17:08.059
I mean, this is getting serious, right?

00:17:08.100 --> 00:17:10.940
Not to just cherry pick, not to just, no, no,

00:17:10.940 --> 00:17:15.419
to do according to all that is written therein.

00:17:15.419 --> 00:17:20.059
And then it says this, for then, then,

00:17:21.619 --> 00:17:24.739
then thou shalt make thy way prosperous

00:17:24.739 --> 00:17:28.579
and then thou shalt have good success.

00:17:30.339 --> 00:17:32.179
Often we want the then,

00:17:33.220 --> 00:17:35.419
but we don't really want the process.

00:17:35.419 --> 00:17:37.019
You know what I mean?

00:17:37.019 --> 00:17:39.299
You read the end of Exodus in chapter 40

00:17:39.299 --> 00:17:41.459
when they're setting up the tabernacle.

00:17:41.459 --> 00:17:43.380
If you read through there, there's three statements

00:17:43.380 --> 00:17:46.059
that are repeated throughout that passage of Scripture

00:17:46.059 --> 00:17:48.019
and you find as you get to the end,

00:17:48.019 --> 00:17:51.859
the Bible says then the glory of the Lord filled the place.

00:17:51.859 --> 00:17:53.220
Well, after what?

00:17:53.220 --> 00:17:55.940
After they did according to what God said.

00:17:56.859 --> 00:17:58.579
And we find here this evening

00:17:58.579 --> 00:18:01.139
that it's an opportunity for us to respond.

00:18:01.139 --> 00:18:04.259
What truth this evening as we consider

00:18:04.259 --> 00:18:06.660
and make preparation our own hearts and spirits

00:18:07.299 --> 00:18:09.500
as we enter into this week of missions conference,

00:18:09.500 --> 00:18:12.220
what truth is there that will be presented

00:18:12.220 --> 00:18:15.299
from this pulpit from one of these men

00:18:15.299 --> 00:18:16.579
that will come and preach?

00:18:16.579 --> 00:18:21.579
What truth is it that we need to implement in our lives?

00:18:21.899 --> 00:18:24.940
That we say, I need that, I need to apply that,

00:18:24.940 --> 00:18:27.500
I need to do that, I need to, listen,

00:18:27.500 --> 00:18:29.299
I've said it before from this pulpit,

00:18:29.299 --> 00:18:31.940
conviction is good for us.

00:18:31.940 --> 00:18:33.460
It is absolutely good for us

00:18:33.460 --> 00:18:36.059
when God steps on our toes and convicts us.

00:18:36.059 --> 00:18:37.500
And by the way, let me say this

00:18:37.500 --> 00:18:39.619
and I'm not saying it just to get a response,

00:18:39.619 --> 00:18:42.739
but the reality is that for us to respond to God,

00:18:42.739 --> 00:18:45.859
for us to use an altar is a good thing.

00:18:45.859 --> 00:18:47.500
It's a good thing.

00:18:47.500 --> 00:18:50.619
It's not embarrassing to go to an altar.

00:18:50.619 --> 00:18:51.700
It's a good thing, why?

00:18:51.700 --> 00:18:53.460
We're doing business with God.

00:18:54.339 --> 00:18:58.299
We understand we don't have to go to an altar,

00:18:58.299 --> 00:19:00.219
but oh, I'm gonna be serious.

00:19:00.219 --> 00:19:03.979
I need what God has in store for us.

00:19:04.020 --> 00:19:07.659
I believe this evening that God's word will be preached

00:19:07.659 --> 00:19:08.820
when these folks come.

00:19:08.820 --> 00:19:10.979
If I didn't believe that they'd preach the Bible,

00:19:10.979 --> 00:19:13.419
if I didn't believe that they would give truth

00:19:13.419 --> 00:19:15.099
from God's word, I wouldn't invite them

00:19:15.099 --> 00:19:17.380
to come stand behind this desk.

00:19:17.380 --> 00:19:19.739
We understand we have revival meetings

00:19:19.739 --> 00:19:21.739
and we have missions conferences,

00:19:21.739 --> 00:19:23.779
we have other guest speakers at different times.

00:19:23.779 --> 00:19:27.059
I am very careful of who I would invite

00:19:27.059 --> 00:19:30.539
to stand behind the desk, the pulpit, the sacred desk

00:19:30.539 --> 00:19:32.339
as we've often referred to it, why?

00:19:32.339 --> 00:19:34.539
Because we need to preach the word.

00:19:34.539 --> 00:19:37.700
It's God's word that changes lives.

00:19:37.700 --> 00:19:39.940
And there's something that's going to be preached

00:19:39.940 --> 00:19:41.979
from this pulpit that I need.

00:19:41.979 --> 00:19:45.619
And I ask myself this question as I have this thought

00:19:45.619 --> 00:19:48.619
of an opportunity to respond to a few thoughts here.

00:19:48.619 --> 00:19:51.460
What part, we need to ask ourselves this personally,

00:19:51.460 --> 00:19:55.419
what part do I have in world missions?

00:19:55.419 --> 00:19:57.020
What part do I have in world missions?

00:19:57.020 --> 00:19:59.500
What am I doing personally

00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:01.100
fulfill the Great Commission?

00:20:02.259 --> 00:20:05.500
I would ask this as we begin to try to answer that,

00:20:05.500 --> 00:20:08.300
do I regularly pray for our missionaries?

00:20:09.300 --> 00:20:13.180
Is it something in my life that is regular

00:20:13.180 --> 00:20:14.739
that I'm praying for missionaries?

00:20:14.739 --> 00:20:17.100
We put together missionary directories

00:20:17.100 --> 00:20:18.780
and we give those to you, why?

00:20:18.780 --> 00:20:21.739
Because we want you to be able to pray for our missionaries.

00:20:21.739 --> 00:20:22.979
We have missionaries of the week

00:20:22.979 --> 00:20:24.819
that we put in our bulletins, why?

00:20:24.819 --> 00:20:25.819
To fill up space?

00:20:25.819 --> 00:20:27.959
No, because we wanna place an emphasis

00:20:27.959 --> 00:20:29.139
that we wanna remind you,

00:20:29.139 --> 00:20:31.520
we need to pray for these missionaries.

00:20:31.520 --> 00:20:33.840
We take the time to put missionary update letters,

00:20:33.840 --> 00:20:35.200
the summaries of those letters

00:20:35.200 --> 00:20:37.599
on the back of our weekly prayer bulletins, why?

00:20:37.599 --> 00:20:40.380
So that you can pray for missionaries.

00:20:40.380 --> 00:20:42.459
And you don't have to pray generically,

00:20:42.459 --> 00:20:44.119
you can pray specifically.

00:20:44.119 --> 00:20:46.020
Do I regularly pray for missionaries?

00:20:46.020 --> 00:20:50.700
Do I regularly give of my finances to support missionaries?

00:20:51.599 --> 00:20:53.119
Can I tell you this evening,

00:20:53.119 --> 00:20:54.919
these missionaries that will come,

00:20:54.919 --> 00:20:57.279
as you know, every missionary that comes here,

00:20:57.299 --> 00:20:59.419
they have a financial need.

00:21:00.500 --> 00:21:03.739
They need to have a certain amount of finances

00:21:03.739 --> 00:21:06.139
to get to the field that God has called them to

00:21:06.139 --> 00:21:08.500
so that they can minister and fulfill the work.

00:21:08.500 --> 00:21:10.160
That's just the reality.

00:21:10.160 --> 00:21:11.660
We understand oftentimes

00:21:11.660 --> 00:21:14.019
when we talk about finances with missionaries,

00:21:14.019 --> 00:21:15.739
we'll talk about their deputation

00:21:15.739 --> 00:21:19.419
and we'll talk about what level support do you have?

00:21:19.419 --> 00:21:20.500
And what are we talking about?

00:21:20.500 --> 00:21:22.360
Well, they have a number that they need to reach

00:21:22.360 --> 00:21:23.860
and they're at a certain percentage

00:21:23.860 --> 00:21:25.540
based on what's already come in.

00:21:25.540 --> 00:21:28.199
One of the missionaries is just at about 70%,

00:21:28.199 --> 00:21:30.080
the Deaton family that will be with us.

00:21:30.080 --> 00:21:31.279
And I believe the Muscott family,

00:21:31.279 --> 00:21:32.440
I believe they're around 90%.

00:21:32.440 --> 00:21:34.480
I haven't gotten an update from him recently.

00:21:34.480 --> 00:21:35.319
But the Deatons,

00:21:35.319 --> 00:21:36.760
I just got an email from them the other day

00:21:36.760 --> 00:21:39.139
and they're right at 70% of their needed support.

00:21:39.139 --> 00:21:41.680
When the Ferringers were here a few weeks ago

00:21:41.680 --> 00:21:43.080
or a month ago,

00:21:43.080 --> 00:21:46.800
they were at like 93.7% or something like that.

00:21:46.800 --> 00:21:48.839
And so we find that these missionaries,

00:21:48.839 --> 00:21:50.639
they need financial support.

00:21:50.639 --> 00:21:52.000
You know, many of these missionaries,

00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:54.940
they cannot go to the field that they're going to

00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:56.319
and get a job.

00:21:56.319 --> 00:21:58.980
They're not permitted to, legally.

00:21:58.980 --> 00:22:01.239
The countries in which they're going to,

00:22:01.239 --> 00:22:04.480
most of them, they will not allow you to enter the country

00:22:04.480 --> 00:22:07.480
if you're going to take from their economy.

00:22:07.480 --> 00:22:08.839
It's just how it works.

00:22:08.839 --> 00:22:10.520
So they need financial support.

00:22:10.520 --> 00:22:11.720
But can I tell you,

00:22:11.720 --> 00:22:14.160
every missionary I've ever spoken to,

00:22:14.160 --> 00:22:16.800
every evangelist that I've ever spoken to,

00:22:16.800 --> 00:22:18.520
more than your financial support,

00:22:18.520 --> 00:22:20.020
they need your prayer support.

00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:23.119
They need your prayer support.

00:22:23.139 --> 00:22:24.100
That's why I ask you,

00:22:24.100 --> 00:22:25.979
do we pray for our missionaries regularly?

00:22:25.979 --> 00:22:28.539
And then do I give of my own resources,

00:22:28.539 --> 00:22:31.059
personally, to support missionaries?

00:22:31.059 --> 00:22:32.539
We can ask ourselves this question,

00:22:32.539 --> 00:22:35.139
do I communicate with any of our missionaries?

00:22:35.139 --> 00:22:37.220
We put email addresses in the bulletins

00:22:37.220 --> 00:22:39.500
on Wednesday evening for the three missionaries of the week.

00:22:39.500 --> 00:22:40.339
Why?

00:22:40.339 --> 00:22:42.580
We put their contact information in the directory.

00:22:42.580 --> 00:22:44.100
Why?

00:22:44.100 --> 00:22:45.419
Because they get lonely.

00:22:46.699 --> 00:22:47.539
And it's good for them to know

00:22:47.539 --> 00:22:49.179
that somebody's praying for them.

00:22:50.119 --> 00:22:53.639
It doesn't have to be a 15 paragraph email.

00:22:53.639 --> 00:22:55.039
It can just be a,

00:22:55.039 --> 00:22:55.960
hey, I just wanted to let you know

00:22:55.960 --> 00:22:57.759
you're a missionary of the week at our church this week

00:22:57.759 --> 00:22:58.960
and I'm praying for you.

00:23:00.639 --> 00:23:04.399
And you have no idea how encouraging that is to a missionary.

00:23:04.399 --> 00:23:08.399
Just absolutely a shot in the arm for them.

00:23:08.399 --> 00:23:09.240
Why?

00:23:09.240 --> 00:23:10.800
Somebody's praying for me.

00:23:10.800 --> 00:23:12.479
Holding the ropes,

00:23:12.479 --> 00:23:16.600
as we've used and seen the analogy used over the years.

00:23:16.600 --> 00:23:18.279
When I think about responding

00:23:18.300 --> 00:23:20.220
and an opportunity to respond,

00:23:20.220 --> 00:23:21.460
there's always this question,

00:23:21.460 --> 00:23:22.899
how can I be more involved?

00:23:22.899 --> 00:23:24.619
What can I do more?

00:23:24.619 --> 00:23:28.139
I don't wanna just become status quo.

00:23:28.139 --> 00:23:31.539
I don't wanna just get stagnant, floundering around.

00:23:31.539 --> 00:23:32.839
I wanna advance.

00:23:32.839 --> 00:23:33.820
I wanna grow.

00:23:33.820 --> 00:23:36.100
I wanna increase.

00:23:36.100 --> 00:23:38.100
I think about the church at Thessalonica.

00:23:38.100 --> 00:23:40.300
The Bible speaks of them of increasing

00:23:40.300 --> 00:23:44.300
and how their faith increaseth exceedingly.

00:23:44.300 --> 00:23:45.580
The Bible speaks of that.

00:23:45.600 --> 00:23:48.479
And the reality is that whatever I'm doing,

00:23:48.479 --> 00:23:50.479
the question that I could ask myself is,

00:23:50.479 --> 00:23:52.679
is there any more that I could do?

00:23:52.679 --> 00:23:55.039
There's any more that I could do.

00:23:55.039 --> 00:23:57.639
So why do we have a missions conference?

00:23:57.639 --> 00:24:01.100
Well, because we're forgetful and we need to be reminded.

00:24:02.380 --> 00:24:06.479
I say we, I'm not saying you, I'm saying we, me.

00:24:06.479 --> 00:24:08.960
We need to be reminded.

00:24:08.960 --> 00:24:12.979
We need to be reminded that God's still working.

00:24:13.000 --> 00:24:16.359
We need to be reminded that God's still calling missionaries.

00:24:16.359 --> 00:24:18.359
We gotta be reminded that people

00:24:18.359 --> 00:24:20.480
are still answering the call.

00:24:20.480 --> 00:24:21.760
These families are gonna stand up here.

00:24:21.760 --> 00:24:22.779
The Muscats are young.

00:24:22.779 --> 00:24:25.160
They have a young daughter,

00:24:25.160 --> 00:24:26.799
probably close to two years old,

00:24:26.799 --> 00:24:27.720
and they're gonna stand up here

00:24:27.720 --> 00:24:30.079
and they're going to another country,

00:24:30.079 --> 00:24:31.540
taking their family there.

00:24:31.540 --> 00:24:33.399
The Deaton family, they're a little bit older.

00:24:33.399 --> 00:24:34.859
They got four children.

00:24:34.859 --> 00:24:36.799
You're gonna see them stand here with their four children.

00:24:36.799 --> 00:24:38.760
They're going to a different country.

00:24:38.760 --> 00:24:40.880
Listen, God's still working.

00:24:40.880 --> 00:24:42.619
We need to be reminded of that.

00:24:43.260 --> 00:24:44.679
It encourages us.

00:24:44.679 --> 00:24:46.359
You're gonna be reminded that we have a part.

00:24:46.359 --> 00:24:48.959
So it's an opportunity for us to be reminded.

00:24:48.959 --> 00:24:51.000
It's an opportunity to refocus

00:24:51.000 --> 00:24:53.200
because we get distracted so easily

00:24:53.200 --> 00:24:56.720
in this fast-paced society that we live in.

00:24:56.720 --> 00:25:00.040
So it's an opportunity to be able to refocus,

00:25:00.040 --> 00:25:01.600
and then it's an opportunity to respond.

00:25:01.600 --> 00:25:03.640
God, what would you have me to do?

00:25:03.640 --> 00:25:06.040
What part can I have in missions?

00:25:06.040 --> 00:25:10.339
What do I need to do with regard to missions?

00:25:10.359 --> 00:25:14.000
God, speak to me, convict me, and God, I'll respond.

00:25:14.000 --> 00:25:17.899
I'll be a doer of the word and not a hearer only.

00:25:17.899 --> 00:25:18.739
Why?

00:25:18.739 --> 00:25:20.239
Because I want to be blessed.

00:25:20.239 --> 00:25:22.239
And we have this missions conference.

00:25:22.239 --> 00:25:23.720
There's a reason for it.

00:25:23.720 --> 00:25:28.720
It's not, there's no book somewhere that I know of anyway

00:25:29.239 --> 00:25:31.359
that says in order to be a good independent Baptist,

00:25:31.359 --> 00:25:33.480
you have to have a missions conference.

00:25:33.480 --> 00:25:34.799
I don't, no, no, no.

00:25:36.000 --> 00:25:36.920
It's because we understand

00:25:36.920 --> 00:25:39.320
that mission is the heartbeat of God.

00:25:39.320 --> 00:25:41.619
And we say, we want to do this

00:25:41.619 --> 00:25:43.140
because we want to be challenged

00:25:43.140 --> 00:25:47.260
and we want to be having this time set apart

00:25:47.260 --> 00:25:50.880
to focus specifically on world evangelism.

00:25:50.880 --> 00:25:52.179
What does God have for us?

00:25:52.179 --> 00:25:53.179
Let's pray together.

00:25:53.179 --> 00:25:54.100
Father, we love you.

00:25:54.100 --> 00:25:55.339
We thank you for loving us.

00:25:55.339 --> 00:25:58.100
Thank you so much for the opportunity

00:25:58.100 --> 00:25:59.940
that we have to gather tonight.

00:25:59.940 --> 00:26:01.220
And then, Lord, we thank you

00:26:01.220 --> 00:26:03.980
that we can have a missions conference.

00:26:04.940 --> 00:26:07.500
And Lord, I pray that you would bless every aspect.

00:26:07.500 --> 00:26:09.760
I pray that you would help us, Lord,

00:26:09.760 --> 00:26:12.200
to honor and glorify you.

00:26:12.200 --> 00:26:14.519
I pray that we'd be spiritually prepared.

00:26:15.480 --> 00:26:18.760
Lord, I pray that you would do a great work

00:26:18.760 --> 00:26:20.000
and we'll thank you for it.

00:26:20.000 --> 00:26:22.920
In Christ's name we pray, amen.

00:26:22.920 --> 00:26:24.320
All right, we're gonna pray.

